item.title: Riester Lied to Police – Washington Times Herald
item.description: The Washington Times Herald Tuesday, July 26, 2011 9:00 am Andrea McCann Riester lied to police [][1] Smith Memorial. Bethaney Deno, Michael Hulsey, and Andrea Jewell built a memorial to their friend, Rhett Smith, who was killed Saturday night on West National Highway. Kelly Overton | The Washington Times Herald Bond was increased to $750,000 Monday for Rachael Riester, 32, who allegedly struck and killed 17-year-old Rhett Smith, 610 Center St.

item.title: Washington Times Herald – Drawing A Crowd
item.description: Drawing a crowd These Washington High School NJROTC cadets drew an attentive crowd while spending part of their summer vacation practicing in front of the Hatchet House at Bedford Road and Seventh Street on Thursday morning. Cadets (from left) are Adam Van Winkle and Adam Chestnut exchanging rifles. At right are cadets Christian Meyer and Ariza Miyasi. Watching in the foreground are (from left) Derek Bruce, Mike Hulsey and Cody Simmons.
